Hey Speed, just wanna say that most Chinese people are actually super, super friendly. But yeah, there’s a tiny group—maybe some with messed-up heads or paid by Western-backed separatists—who mix in with the crowd and might affect your trip to China a bit. Still, I hope you can brush off those bad moments and keep the good memories!

For example, those who can chat with you in English? They’re not your average Chinese folks. Even though we’ve been taught English forever, most Chinese barely use it to speak, and they don’t really get your culture. So, anyone throwing out rude words or doing disrespectful stuff—they’re not normal people here.

Funny thing—this message was translated by Grok for me. I can’t type it in English myself, even after studying it from middle school to college!

Anyway, hope you have a blast in China! Would be awesome if you could show the real China to America and the Western world. Cheers!
